<subSubSection box="[796,1318,301,330]" pageId="90" pageNumber="368" type="distribution">
<caption box="[796,1318,301,330]" inLine="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="368" targetBox="[822,826,1019,1040]" targetPageId="90">
<paragraph blockId="90.[795,1387,301,724]" box="[796,1318,301,330]" pageId="90" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[796,972,301,330]" pageId="90" pageNumber="368">Distribution.</emphasis>
Restricted to E Panama.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="90" pageNumber="368" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="90.[795,1387,301,724]" pageId="90" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[796,1037,336,369]" pageId="90" pageNumber="368">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body c.62-65 mm, tail 100-112 mm, ear 14-15 mm, hindfoot 17-19 mm; weight 10 g. The Darien Har vest Mouse is medium-sized. Dorsum is pale brown, with peppered or streaked pattern. Venter varies from white to orangecinnamon. Tail is long compared to that of the Slender Harvest Mouse (
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen &amp; F. M. Chapman" authorityYear="1897" box="[1237,1372,616,645]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Reithrodontomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="90" pageNumber="368" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gracilis">R. gracilis</taxonomicName>
). Rastrum and braincase are shorter than in the Slender Harvest Mouse.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="90" pageNumber="368" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="90.[180,1385,739,1040]" pageId="90" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[182,293,739,764]" pageId="90" pageNumber="368">Habitat.</emphasis>
Lowland tropical deciduous forests with dense stands of oaks (
<taxonomicName box="[1274,1380,739,764]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="90" pageNumber="368" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Quercus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[182,310,774,803]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="90" pageNumber="368" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
) interspersed with shrubs and grasses up to elevations of ¢.900 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
